column_.text_:
As we fly closer to the main island, an ocean of sand seems
to stretch on forever.

As we fly closer to the main island, an ocean of sand seems
to stretch on forever.
Large ruins break the surface like icebergs.
Large ruins break the surface like icebergs.

It's time to start digging through the past.
'Cause in one of those tombs...
Lies the catalyst to our future.

It's time to start digging through the past.
'Cause in one of those tombs...
Lies the catalyst to our future.
Last stop: Dahli.
Time to dig up that catalyst! For Lyria!

We must find that catalyst. I won't allow them to control
Lyria any longer!

Tch, that beardo thinks he can boss me around? Well, I'm
doin' this for Lyria!
Hang in there, Lyria. We'll make you all better again!

That mind sealer thing pisses me off. The sooner we find the
catalyst, the better.
A world without Lyria's smile is no world at all.
Geegee and Beppo will be perfect for searching tight places.

Marching through a desert is no easy task. Everyone, stay
hydrated.
I love treasure hunts! Can't wait to start digging!

I still do not fully trust Zathba but... Right now, he is our only
hope of finding the catalyst.

Desert creatures have adapted to their harsh environs. They
will be formidable.
Lyria cries for rescue! Let us crash through the dunes!

This sandbox is a bit big for one lonely crew to rummage
through, don'tcha think? Oh, well. Anything for Lyria.

I don't do well with heat... But for Lyria, I would walk through
fire and brimstone.

Haha! Tomb raiding, eh? My fists shall blast us back to the
past!

Find the catalyst thingy so we can restore Lyria back to
normal. Got it. No sweat.

Would be amazing luck if the catalyst happened to be right in
front of us. Never that simple though, is it?

I wonder what kind of contraption this catalyst is. Can't wait
to get my hands on it.
Time to move.
I don't wanna melt, so let's get movin'.

It's like lookin' for a needle in a haystack at a haystack
convention.
Almost took a spill there.

Actually... surfin' down dunes might save us time. Just don't
wipe out and eat sand.
Uh-oh. Is that a pack of wolves?
We've been spotted! Get ready to fight!
Heads up! They're callin' for more furry friends!

This is probably their territory. Hush them up before they
alert the whole desert!

We've got the jump on them! Now's our chance to end this
swiftly!

This trail looks promising. I once read that treasure's always
buried off the beaten path.

I don't think there's anything here. On second thought, do we
even know what the catalyst looks like?
Are you sure we've thoroughly searched this area?

At least we didn't come away empty-handed. I'm thinkin' it's
time to move on.
No point sticking around here. Move out, people.
Wouldn't shock me if we've picked this place clean.

Are you still looking for something? I think we've already
done a clean sweep.
Over there! Looks like a way into the ruins!

Remember the seals Zathba was talking about? They may
be around here.
Nice and cool! A little shade makes all the difference.

When was this structure built? Despite the wear and tear, it
doesn't seem that old to me.

Probably has a complicated history. Like every other tomb
with buried treasure.
Aaugh!
Aaaah!
What!
Oh crap!
Eeeek!
Argh!
Oh no!
Aaaah!
It's collapsing!
Waugh!
No!
Protect your heads!
Yaaah!
My word!
This can't be!
Graah!
No way!
Damn.
Seriously?!
Tch!
Whoooa! If I wanted to go surfing, I'd have flown to Auguste!

There's no way to stop sliding! Just try to maintain your
balance!

I see you found the golden carpet the desert rolls out for its
guests. Enjoy the slide.
What does that mean? Did you set a trap for us?
And what would I gain from that? Don't worry; you'll be fine.
Ugh! You're the last person I'd trust!

Trust or not, all we can do is slide. We're just gonna have to
play it by ear!
Wait a second! Vyrn can fly! If we all grab onto him...
Um... I'm only one dragon, Katalina!
Cliff! Clifff!
Aaaagh!
Gyaaah!
Aaaah!
I wanted off, but not like this!
I'm gonna kill that beardo!
I'm too old for high divin'!
Hold fast! We can survive this!
We can survive this, everyone!
No! It's too steep!
Waaaugh!
Hah. I will not die here!
Aim for the piles of sand!
A Holy Knight fears nothiiing!
Nobody panic. The sand'll cushion us!
Get ready to tuck and roll, everyone!
A Ghandagoza always lands on his feet!
This isn't happening! This isn't happening!
Prepare for landing.
Wheee! Cag wuvs slides!
I'll stick the landing.

You folks got guts. That shortcut's known for being, um...
lethal.
Don't screw with us. The floor gave out and you know it.

Well, whatever the circumstances, it saved you time—and
that's worth celebrating. Good business is all about
efficiency.

I mean, you're not wrong. We need as much time as we can
get. Are we still goin' the right way?
Yep. Up ahead you'll see something that looks like a door.
Huh? What's that glowy thing on the floor?

That's the "key" to moving forward. Stand on it for a bit and
watch the ruins come alive.

Is this the light of a primal? What kind of place have we
wandered into?
Well, I'll be. The door's opening.
Holy moly! This place is way bigger than I thought!

See that platform smack-dab in the middle of the desert?
You gotta light the whole thing up.

The contraption you're after is probably sleeping soundly
beneath it.

After you break the seal, we'll be collecting our treasure.
Sound simple enough?

Yes, in theory... But we all know these sorts of places are
riddled with traps.

Nothing's free in life. You want the catalyst, you gotta work
for it.

A skyfarer's job never ends. Keep one hand on your weapon
at all times.

Hey, it'd be boring if all we did was step on tiles. Let's start
by exploring up ahead.
Bwuh? What just happened!

What peculiar wind magic... Perhaps this mechanism was
used as a form of transportation?
That oughta make desert-surfing a breeze.
Whoa! You okay?
Man! It's hard to control once you get goin'.
You know what they say: practice makes perfect.
Yahoo! That's what I call express service!
That was awesome! Where can I learn to use magic like that?
Are you folks working or playing?
Eeep! Momma!
Poor Rackam. So scared you can't take a little leap of faith?

If people were meant to fly, they'd have wings! Helming the
Grandcypher is enough thrill for me!
Hahaha! Can we do that again?
Heh. Nothin' like givin' a mighty boot to the face!

This'd be a perfect sniping spot. Got a clear line of sight in
every direction.

It's easy to get lost in this expanse. Keep an eye on any
useful landmarks.
Why couldn't Zathba drop us off here to begin with?

I gave you valuable intel as a down payment. Least you can
do is show me I made a wise investment.
Hah. Touché.
I think I'm starting to burn.
Indeed... The desert's wrecking havoc on our skin.
Right! Let's crack that seal and find some shade ASAP!

Is everyone still feeling okay? If not, we can always return to
hallowed ground.

Goin' from freezing mountains to sweltering deserts ain't
doin' my body any favors.

It almost feels like primal power is sprinkled in with the
sands and ruins...

Residue from the Dahli catastrophe. Leveled the island one
night fifteen years ago.
Holy mackerel. What in the world happened?
Ah-ah-ah. Any non-work related info is gonna cost extra.
Fine, whatever. I didn't wanna know that bad anyway.

It's so hard walking through sand. It keeps getting in my
shoes.
Don't I know it. Gonna have to give my gun a full cleaning.
So thirsty...

Uh-oh. Always stay hydrated when you're in the desert.
Otherwise you'll be easy pickings for monsters.

By the way, Zathba, may I ask how you learned about the
mind sealer and catalyst?

C'mon now, a broker never reveals his sources. Let's just
say I got a history with this place.

This desert is much bigger than I thought. We'd be lost
without Zathba nudging us in the right direction.

Y'know, I've been wondering why the catalyst is buried
here... This island must have some impressive backstory.
I could sure go for a cold one...

What do you say, "barkeep"? Buy us a round after a hard
day's work?

My bar's fully stocked, but anything more than water, well,
that comes down to your performance.
So how'd you folks get mixed up with Rolan anyhow?

It's not that interesting. When we first came to this skydom,
we bumped into him on Folca.
We're lucky to have met him. He's been nothing but helpful.

Heh. The man's too kind for his own good. Always sticking
his neck out for people.
So... How do you know Rolan, Zathba?

We're both softies at heart. Two idealists in the business of
making the world a better place.

With Avia mucking things up these days, it seemed like a
no-brainer to team up for a bit.

I know there's all kinds of skyfarers out there, but you folks
are special.
Wait, was that a compliment? Thanks!

You've got grit. I hope my own boys are learning a thing or
two from you.

Man, there's a world of difference when you get in the shade!
It's at least a thousand degrees cooler.
It's too bad we can't chill out here forever.
Huh? What's that?
Get back! It's venomous!
It looks super tough! Do we fight or run?
I just wanna say that I refuse to be snake chow.

Desert hunters know how to camouflage themselves. Watch
where you step.

We defeated this one, but there could be more lurking
beneath our feet.
This is like the worst vacation spot ever.
I think it got tired of chasin' us.

Hey, no shame in hightailing it. Those poison rotters don't
play fair.
Waugh! We're under attack!
Watch out! It's venomous!
Phew... I hate surprises like that.
This terrain gives monsters the perfect cover for ambushes.
Ack! Here comes another one!

This place is crawling with wigglers. Move slowly, and keep
your eyes on the sand.
Hah! Hurts, don't it!
We got the element of surprise!
It's an air raid!

An earth spirit... No doubt its powers are augmented by this
land.
It's an army of bones! We're surrounded!

If we use the terrain wisely, we can split them off into
smaller groups!

Was that all of them? Hope we didn't stumble onto ancient
burial grounds.
Rest in pieces, you bone-ified jerks.
I think we got away somehow.
Avoid needless battles and live to fight another day.
Oh, geez! More undead? I had my fill back at the mountain!
Psst! Quiet! You'll wake it up!
Actually, maybe we should give it a rude awakening.
Welp, it's awake now. Get ready!

Maybe it wants breakfast? Let's not get squished into
pancakes!
What the!
We've got a party crasher! Get ready for double duty!
That takes care of half the threat. Now for the other half!
Wow, that was scary. One of 'em came out of nowhere.

Perhaps it was hunting us. Just goes to show anything can
happen out here.
So we need to make this whole circle glow, huh?
You got it. It's basically a trapdoor to the vault.

Once you activate all the keys, the door will unlock, and that
sweet, sweet treasure will be mine.
Uh, you mean there's more than one key?

Yep. Remember the first one you stepped on? Just do that a
few more times.
And they're scattered throughout this whole desert...

At least our sight lines are clear. Should be easy enough to
spot them.
Part of the circle's lit up! That switch we activated worked!

Good. Then you already know what to do. Light up the rest so
we can get inside.

We're makin' good progress. We'll have this baby fully
shimmerin' in no time.
Look! Up there!
Is that... a griffin?

I'll tell you what it is: trouble. Ranged attacks are our best bet
against that flyin' beast.
It's here! Weapons out!
It's flappin' around like crazy! Stay sharp!
Move to intercept! Watch for aerial attacks!
Zigzag all you want, but I've got you in my crosshairs!
Try dodging my magic, bird brain!
It's just like huntin' ducks! Big old angry ducks!
Poor thing. You should've flown the coop!

Wyverns, griffins... There's no monster my whip can't
tame!

It's nimble, all right. As soon as it gets within range, strike
quickly and decisively!
Sorry! Our friend needs help, and you're kinda in the way!

My flames may course to the core of the earth... Or ascend to
the brightest heavens.

With flying enemies, the trick is to never let them out of your
sight.
Soar all you want! You cannot fly higher than a Holy Knight!
An air battle, eh? Nice change of pace from reelin' in fish!

Remember, every moment wasted here is a moment away
from Lyria... No mercy!

Against a mighty bird of prey, one must be as swift and
subtle as a viper!
Oh, please. It's just a big dumb bird! I'll roast it—extra crispy!
This one's fast. Keep an eye on the skies.

So what if this is your nesting spot? Shouldn't have built it in
our damn way.
I'll take it down.
Keep pouring it on! It can only take so much punishment!
Oof... Big monsters always pack a wallop.
Come now. Time to activate the key.
Trying to activate the key while duking it out? I'm impressed.

It's called killing two birds with one stone! Whether we pull it
off is a different story!

It's glowing. Must run on the same magic as the gate at the
entrance.

Looks like we're halfway there. Let's just hope nothing
interrupts us.
Only halfway? Pick up the pace!
Halfway there! Keep standing on that switch!
Almost there!
This is making me restless...
Good, good. Just a little more.

Look. It's losing power. We need to stay on the switch until
the device is fully charged.

But that means no running, dodging, or jumping. Might
wanna activate the key after we've won the fight.
No! The light is fading away!
Let it go for now. Our priority should be to secure the area.
Now where were we on that key?
Hey, don't forget to activate the key.
Good work. We're making even better time than I'd hoped.
Fantastic. Keep it up. Hang tight, treasure, Papa's comin'.
He's a like a whole new person when it comes to money...
Look at all these buildings.

There could be a treasure trove of rare stuff. Let's dig
around.
Hold on! Something's coming!
Where'd that monster come from? It's not like the others!

Stay on your guard. The dead are dangerous foes—they've
got nothing left to lose.

Will it curse me if I get too close? Y'know, I think I'll just
shoot it from here.

It's practically radiating dark energy. This skelly is bad to the
bone!

Would you call it big-boned or shredded? Eh, who cares.
Let's just blow the damn thing up.

This wretch was likely a powerful warrior in life... Why would
it be bound to a place like this?

I know what it's like to be a lost spirit. C'mon, everyone, let's
put its soul to rest.

Don't be daunted by the size of its axe. What it gains in force,
it sacrifices in speed!
What do you call the skeleton boss? The bone-head!

What does size matter? The vessel of your spirit will burn, be
it made of flesh or bone.
This poor soul has suffered long enough. Let's lay it to rest.

This revenant is particularly formidable! I shall purify its soul
with my holy sword!
Finally, an opponent with a little backbone! Wahaha!

Our world can offer nothing to this spirit but memories of
pain and bloodshed. Let us release it to the hereafter.

A fallen warrior, eh? What say you to one last brawl? I'll
pummel away your last regrets!

Looks like this stiff isn't ready to move on just yet. My fire
can help with that.
Holding grudges isn't worth it. Let me purge yours for you.
A colossal skeleton? How scawy! Let's grind it into dust!
I'll bury you!
Its movements aren't as sharp as before! Press the attack!
I've got an axe to grind with this one. No bones about it!
No comment.
That thing gave me the willies.
Credit where credit's due; it was no lazybones.
Sigh...

You done clearing out mooks? Then hightail it over to the
key.
Did this used to be a tower?

Probably. And judging from the look of these ruins, it
collapsed in a large explosion...

Look at how the walls are ornamented. Chances are, this
was a temple or other place of worship.
So you're saying they were holy? Give me a break!

That's a weird looking piece of rubble. What do ya think it
used to be?

A grand building, no doubt. All that beauty, lost forever... It
just breaks my heart.

Findin' treasure in a place like this would be a surefire way to
boost the land value.

Speak of the devil! A chest! Should change my job to
professional relic hunter.
Haha, I like the sound o' that.
Okay, that's... a golem.

Or this skydom's version of one. I wonder if they imported
the technology from Erste...

Was it guarding something? Please don't move... Please
don't move...
Yikes! It's alive!
That's one tough customer, but we're tougher!

Try to fight it without getting too close. If that thing manages
to corner us, it's all over!

I jinxed it, didn't I? Well, now that sleeping beauty's awake,
it's time for a ball!
It could've kept right on dreaming, but nooo...
What's done is done! Might as well finish the wake-up call!

You don't want anyone stepping on the key? Aw, well, that's
too bad!

Is there an off button? No? Then I guess we're gonna have to
total it!
I'll be the decoy. Strike as soon as there's an opening!
Rock-a-bye-gooolem... What? It was worth a try!
I shall bend it to my will... Or break it all to pieces.
Draw your weapons! We'll have to force our way through!

I respect this guardian's dedication to duty. But for dear
Lyria, we must break through!
Fine, fine. I don't mind a game of tag! Hey! I'm over here!
What is rock and stone against an unbreakable will?
Gahahaha! Are you a fighter worth your salt?

You shoulda just kept your head down. Then I wouldn't have
to bust your stones!

This golem doesn't seem happy with us. I'll try to draw its
fury.

Compared to my homunculi, this scrap heap's got the
sophistication of a mud pie.
You know what to do.

This is a tough nut to crack! I mean, it is practically a living
rock...

Whew... That was a close battle, but we managed to pull
through.
Booyah! All that's left is to activate the key!

Check out that altar. My money says it holds the gizmo you're
looking for.
Nice job. Good help is hard to find these days.

Now head back to the central ruins and grab the loot. I've got
a date with that treasure chest.
Now for the moment of truth. That catalyst better be there.
Should be sitting pretty on its own tailor-made pedestal.

I don't care what you grab first; just don't forget to bring us
back our box of riches.

Once we have the catalyst, it's only a matter of time before
Lyria's free again.

Disaster has a habit of rearing its ugly head on the home
stretch. Don't celebrate till it's over.

Whatcha staring at the sand for? We gotta get back to the
central ruins!

Get your keisters in gear! You're not the only treasure
hunters in these skies.
Not these punks again. If you want a beating, we'll oblige!
You took the words right from my mouth.
Huh?
That stone is a captivating prize.
Unfortunately, I can't allow you to claim it.
You may call me Maglielle. And these are my kindred.
The Sword Veil.
And we wish to show you our beautiful bladework.
Do enjoy yourselves to the fullest.
Teach them a lesson they shall never forget.
With pleasure.

I'm so sick of all these jerks getting in our way! Send 'em
packing!

There must be a secret to their technique. Watch carefully
and figure it out!

Griffins, golems, and sword goons! It's time for this damn
circus act to end!

Finally! Ever since we escaped that mountain, I've been
itching for payback!

When we bury you in the sand, just remember... You asked
for it!
Their swordplay is almost hypnotic... Don't get pulled in!

Back again? Looks like this time, I'll have to teach you a
lesson you won't forget!

This fight's going to get desperate. Don't get separated from
the group!

Listen, I might never go looking for a fight—but I also never
back down from one!

Hah. You have no hope of stopping us. Do not mistake your
cheap tricks for power!
They may have the numbers—but we have the conviction.

The art of war is my forte. As captain of the Lumiel Order, I
will lead our forces to triumph!
Heeheehee! The more the merrier, I always say!
Stay close to me. I'll cut through their lines!
Aw, where's the thrill in wiping out riff-raff with one punch?
Don't these losers have anything else better to do!
They've made their beds. It's time they lay in them.
Heat and crowds? That's the perfect formula for death!
This desert's gonna be your tomb!

We musta taken out a whole platoon by now. Where are they
comin' from?
It doesn't matter! We have to break through!
Maglielle didn't become an Avia general by being a pushover.

She and her squad have tricks up their sleeves. Don't
underestimate them.
It's not over until I say it is.

Fresh boots on the ground! You know the drill! Divide and
conquer!
Hey! Don't hurt that treasure chest!
Last one!
I have failed... My lady...
Oh, very well. Since you insist upon testing the Sword Veil...
It's my honor to expose your hubris!

Geez, that's a lotta swords. No wonder she's the head
honcho!

If we can take down a general, we'll cripple a third of Avia's
forces!

Thanks for sending us down the scenic route back at the
mountain. How much do we owe you?

Wah, cry some more. You're not getting that catalyst—not in
a million years!

You pick a fight, get your ass kicked, and now you're pissed?
Yeah, real mature!

A flying dervish among infinite blades... Whets my thorns just
thinking about it.

We warned you! We won't stop at anything until Lyria's
home again.

She may be a general... But that's all the more reason to stay
calm and focused.

Don't, uhh, stare at the spinny swords too long. They make
you dizzy...

A king never forgets his debts. Now comes the hour of my
vengeance!
No more games. The catalyst is coming with us.

You chose the wrong skyfarers to antagonize! We will end
your reign of terror!

That lass is no stranger to danger. I'm keen to test out her
skills!
Run, or face death.
Gahaha! Our battle shall be legendary!
I'm gonna wipe that smirk right off your face!
Hm... She's on equal footing with Gallanza. Enough said.

Hey, mind if I play with your toys? Wait, why bother asking
for permission if I'm just gonna pick 'em off your corpse?
Maggie... Let's settle this!
Your spirit is impressive, but how long before it breaks?

She's holdin' us back all by herself! Avia generals are no
joke!

My, my, this is all it takes to impress you? I haven't even
broken a sweat.

The peerless choreography of my magic swords shall
bedazzle and pierce your hearts!

I did not think you would last this long. I can see why
Gallanza likes you so much.

His lust for battle makes him rather reckless, doesn't it? I,
however, am always in control!
Ergh! Why won't you die!

Did you honestly think you were gonna stop us with a bunch
of glorified needles?

Failure will not be tolerated... As the primeval god is my
witness...
Wait, she can make shields with those slicers?

But of course. My blades hold infinite potential. Though... it
takes a true visionary to see that.

Those magic swords keep bouncing whatever we throw at
her!

I know they look formidable, but remember: no defense is
flawless.
How dare you scuff my blades!
Even the sturdiest shield can be broken! Charge forward!

Smash those swords! The fewer she has, the weaker her
defenses!

We managed to punch holes in her sword wall. Now it's time
to bring the storm!
All of her swords have shattered! It's now or never!
Aw yeah! Sock it to her!
What's the matter? Upset that you lost all your toys?
Arise, my lovely blades!
And now, for act two.
I would have been happy stopping at act one.
This again. How many swords can one person own?
We know how to deal with it! Don't be discouraged!
I grow weary of this force.
Weapons of legend, assemble!
Hah!
To battle!
Hammer of thunder... Mjolnir!
Pistol of demons... Freikugel
Stave of divinity... Caduceus!
Spear of legends... Gae Bulg!

The stage is set for the big bang. Come one,
come all.
Let's enjoy the show!
Let us begin.
Go, my legends. Delight in chaos.
Huh!
Now, come!
O godmallet whose belly quakes with thunder! Smash them all!
O pistol whose history is painted in red! Pierce them through!
O stave whose divinity is made manifest! Unburden their souls!
O spear whose legend is shrouded in shadow! Devastate their bodies!
The final waltz is upon us...
Symphony Superiór!

It's a madhouse out here! I'm havin' a hard time keepin' track
of everything!

If we don't destroy those weapons, she'll have us dancing to
her tune all day.
We took out one of the weapons!
Grr! I worked so hard to get that for my collection!
Aaah! How can you treat a masterpiece like that!
Nggh... It's bad enough I took it out of its case...
Does the name "superlative weapon" mean nothing to you?!

You leave me no choice. Once more I call upon the
superlative weapons!

I would prefer to not expose my collection to further damage,
but this is the only way to defeat you!
Fortune favors the bold. Together, we shall achieve victory!
Mind if I crank up the tempo a little?
Go out and mingle! Everyone loves a sharp partner!
Frolic, my blades. Dance until all have fallen!
Any way you slice it, I will be the last one standing!

It's almost time for the grand finale! I'm on the edge of my
seat!
Secret of the veil, reveal thyself! Sword Opera!
Ngh... I missed a step...
You people lack grace...
You haven't won yet!
I'm the one running the show here.
You need to learn how to be a better dance partner.
That should do for a few measures of rest.
What absurd power!
Now you've done it. I shall return that licking twofold.
Is this how you got Gallanza to fall to his knees?
How are you all so in sync with your attacks?
They assail with such fervent tempo!
Impossible! I am stronger than this!

Thank you for a lovely soiree. I can always host another one
if you are so inclined.
I will... not...
Ta-da!

With this doohickey, we should be able to get the old Lyria
back!
Come in, crew! Is everyone all right?
Hey, it's Rolan! Is the Grandcypher back to 100%?
Yes, we're on our way over right now.
You're gettin' it done. Thanks, pal!
So, any news on the catalyst?

We sorta ran into a minor hiccup, but it's safe in our hands
now!
That's what I like to hear.

Great job out there, everyone! I'm coming to pick you up
now!
Thanks, we'll be waitin'.
Roger!
I won't fail!
Everybody run!
My lady!
Fall back.
What is it this time!
That doesn't look right from up here... Oh no...
Listen to me! You all need to get out of—
Crap—Move it!
We gotta jump!
No, no, no, no, no... This is not happening!
Hey, Boss?
Feels like overkill for a glorified treasure warden.
Incoming!
Too late!
Oh, momma!
Phew! Made it just in time!
Rolan!
Cutting it a little bit close there, huh?
Berate me later. Let's provide air support!
Roger.
No way...
Careful up there! It's trackin' ya!
What the hell am I looking at?

That's primeval god Excavallion, the divine guardian of this
land.
